narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you liked DS in the fall, you'll probably like it in the spring.
It is an excellent class. I would definitely recommend other students to take it.
Amazing reading list, aside from Petrarch.

This is an intensive survey of the modern half the the western literary canon. I would fully recommend this class to any student because it provides a perfect background for any field in the humanities.

Some great books on the syllabus. Class is ok. Would take it again because I'd take DS again, but I wouldn't take this on its own. To be fair, I wouldn't really take a Lit class on its own for any reason. So I'd guess this class is better than most Lit classes. Take DS tho.
